{
  "abstract": "Peanut bud necrosis disease (PBND) is an economically important virus disease of groundnut (Arachis hypogaea L.) caused by Peanut bud necrosis Virus (PBNV) (Groundnut bud necrosis virus), a member of genus Tospovirus for which no durable resistance has been found among the available germplasm accessions",
